Event Summary



On 14 June 2025, after 40 days of protests and blockades in the province of Bocas del Toro, the national government decided to carry out a police operation to clear the roads.
Journalists and cameramen from three media outlets, who went to cover the event, were punched in the face by the people blocking the streets . They were also threatened with rocks and robbed of their equipment in an attempt to prevent them from continuing to film. Some of the protesters later returned the equipment to the cameramen.
The journalists were taken to a safe location by the National Aeronaval Service.
In a statement issued by journalistic associations on 16 June 2025, it is mentioned that during the first two weeks of June, several instances of intimidation and, in some cases, physical attacks against journalists have been reported throughout the country during coverage of protests by demonstrators.
